                                    <div class="solar-item__info">
                                        <h4 class="solar-item__name">The Sun is the most prominent feature in our solar
                                            system. It is the largest object and contains approximately 98% of the total
                                            solar system mass. One hundred and nine Earths would be required to fit
                                            across the Sun's disk, and its interior could hold over 1.3 million Earths.
                                            The Sun's outer visible layer is called the photosphere and has a
                                            temperature of 6,000°C (11,000°F).</h4>
                                        <h1>Sun Introduction</h1>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
